"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# WebSockets API\\n\\nThe WebSockets API provides data feeds providing the trader real-time information.\\n\\nSee the [guide](/interaction/data/feeds) for examples on how to use the WebSockets API.\\n\\n## Common schemas\\n\\nInteractions with the WebSockets endpoint is done using common base JSON schemas for all channels/feed types.\\nFor specific feeds, see the following [subsections](#feeds).\\n\\n### Subscribe\\n\\nUse the following schema to subscribe to a channel.\\n\\n#### JSON Schema\\n\\n| Parameter           | Type               | Description                                                           |\\n| ------------------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `type`              | string             | Message type (`subscribe`).                                           |\\n| `channel`           | string             | Feed type identifier.                                                 |\\n| `id`                | string             | Selector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.       |\\n| `batched`           | bool               | Reduce incoming messages by batching contents.                        |\\n\\n:::details[Example]\\n```tsx\\n{ \\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"subscribe\\\", \\n    \\\"channel\\\": \\\"v4_trades\\\",\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"BTC-USD\\\",\\n    \\\"batched\\\": false\\n}\\n```\\n:::\\n\\n#### Response\\n\\n| Parameter           | Type               | Description                                                           |\\n| ------------------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `type`              | string             | Message type (`subscribed`).                                          |\\n| `connection_id`     | string             | String identifying the subscription.                                  |\\n| `message_id`        | int                | Message sequence number sent on the subscription.                     |\\n| `id`                | string             | Selector for channel-specific data.                                   |\\n| `contents`          | value              | Channel-specific initial data.                                        |\\n\\n### Unsubscribe\\n\\nUse the following schema to unsubscribe from a channel.\\nSimilar scheme to the `subscribe` schema, however with the `unsubscribe` type, and without the `batched` field.\\n\\n#### JSON Schema\\n\\n| Parameter           | Type               | Description                                                           |\\n| ------------------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `type`              | string             | Message type (`unsubscribe`).                                         |\\n| `channel`           | string             | Feed type identifier.                                                 |\\n| `id`                | string             | Selector for channel-specific data.                                   |\\n\\n:::details[Example]\\n```tsx\\n{\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"unsubscribe\\\",\\n    \\\"channel\\\": \\\"v4_trades\\\",\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"BTC-USD\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n:::\\n\\n#### Response\\n\\n| Parameter           | Type               | Description                                                           |\\n| ------------------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `type`              | string             | Message type (`unsubscribed`).                                        |\\n| `connection_id`     | string             | String identifying the subscription.                                  |\\n| `channel`           | string             | Feed type identifier.                                                 |\\n| `message_id`        | int                | Message sequence number sent on the subscription.                     |\\n| `id`                | string             | Selector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.       |\\n\\n### Data\\n\\nAfter subscription, the incoming messages will be serialized using the following schema.\\n\\n#### JSON Schema\\n\\n| Parameter           | Type               | Description                                                           |\\n| ------------------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| `connection_id`     | string             | String identifying the subscription.                                  |\\n| `channel`           | string             | Feed type identifier.                                                 |\\n| `id`                | string             | Selector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.       |\\n| `message_id`        | int                | Message sequence number sent on the subscription.                     |\\n| `version`           | string             | Protocol identifier.                                                  |\\n| `contents`          | value              | Channel-specific message data.                                        |\\n\\n## Channels\\n\\nThe available clients API is presented below.\\nFor each, the subscription and unsubscription functions are shown. Internally, these functions send messages serialized in the [subscribe](#json-schema) and [unsubscribe](#json-schema-1) JSON schemas above.\\n\\nFor each channel/feed type the sub-schemas employed in the `contents` field of the received [Data](#json-schema-2) (after subscription) are shown. \\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#websockets-api\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>The WebSockets API provides data feeds providing the trader real-time information.</p>\\n<p>See the <a href=\\\"/interaction/data/feeds\\\">guide</a> for examples on how to use the WebSockets API.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#websockets-api\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nThe WebSockets API provides data feeds providing the trader real-time information.\\nSee the guide for examples on how to use the WebSockets API.\\n\",\"title\":\"WebSockets API\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#common-schemas\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Interactions with the WebSockets endpoint is done using common base JSON schemas for all channels/feed types.\\nFor specific feeds, see the following <a href=\\\"#feeds\\\">subsections</a>.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#common-schemas\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nInteractions with the WebSockets endpoint is done using common base JSON schemas for all channels/feed types.\\nFor specific feeds, see the following subsections.\\n\",\"title\":\"Common schemas\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#subscribe\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Use the following schema to subscribe to a channel.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#subscribe\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nUse the following schema to subscribe to a channel.\\n\",\"title\":\"Subscribe\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#json-schema\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>type</code></td><td>string</td><td>Message type (<code>subscribe</code>).</td></tr><tr><td><code>channel</code></td><td>string</td><td>Feed type identifier.</td></tr><tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>Selector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.</td></tr><tr><td><code>batched</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Reduce incoming messages by batching contents.</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n<details><summary>Example</summary><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{ </span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;type&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;subscribe&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">, </span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;channel&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;v4_trades&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;id&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;BTC-USD&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;batched&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">false</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre></details>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#json-schema\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nParameterTypeDescriptiontypestringMessage type (subscribe).channelstringFeed type identifier.idstringSelector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.batchedboolReduce incoming messages by batching contents.\\nExample{ \\n    &quot;type&quot;: &quot;subscribe&quot;, \\n    &quot;channel&quot;: &quot;v4_trades&quot;,\\n    &quot;id&quot;: &quot;BTC-USD&quot;,\\n    &quot;batched&quot;: false\\n}\\n\",\"title\":\"JSON Schema\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\",\"Subscribe\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#response\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>type</code></td><td>string</td><td>Message type (<code>subscribed</code>).</td></tr><tr><td><code>connection_id</code></td><td>string</td><td>String identifying the subscription.</td></tr><tr><td><code>message_id</code></td><td>int</td><td>Message sequence number sent on the subscription.</td></tr><tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>Selector for channel-specific data.</td></tr><tr><td><code>contents</code></td><td>value</td><td>Channel-specific initial data.</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#response\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nParameterTypeDescriptiontypestringMessage type (subscribed).connection_idstringString identifying the subscription.message_idintMessage sequence number sent on the subscription.idstringSelector for channel-specific data.contentsvalueChannel-specific initial data.\\n\",\"title\":\"Response\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\",\"Subscribe\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#unsubscribe\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Use the following schema to unsubscribe from a channel.\\nSimilar scheme to the <code>subscribe</code> schema, however with the <code>unsubscribe</code> type, and without the <code>batched</code> field.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#unsubscribe\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nUse the following schema to unsubscribe from a channel.\\nSimilar scheme to the subscribe schema, however with the unsubscribe type, and without the batched field.\\n\",\"title\":\"Unsubscribe\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#json-schema-1\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>type</code></td><td>string</td><td>Message type (<code>unsubscribe</code>).</td></tr><tr><td><code>channel</code></td><td>string</td><td>Feed type identifier.</td></tr><tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>Selector for channel-specific data.</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n<details><summary>Example</summary><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;type&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;unsubscribe&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;channel&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;v4_trades&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">    &quot;id&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;BTC-USD&quot;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre></details>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#json-schema-1\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nParameterTypeDescriptiontypestringMessage type (unsubscribe).channelstringFeed type identifier.idstringSelector for channel-specific data.\\nExample{\\n    &quot;type&quot;: &quot;unsubscribe&quot;,\\n    &quot;channel&quot;: &quot;v4_trades&quot;,\\n    &quot;id&quot;: &quot;BTC-USD&quot;\\n}\\n\",\"title\":\"JSON Schema\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\",\"Unsubscribe\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#response-1\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>type</code></td><td>string</td><td>Message type (<code>unsubscribed</code>).</td></tr><tr><td><code>connection_id</code></td><td>string</td><td>String identifying the subscription.</td></tr><tr><td><code>channel</code></td><td>string</td><td>Feed type identifier.</td></tr><tr><td><code>message_id</code></td><td>int</td><td>Message sequence number sent on the subscription.</td></tr><tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>Selector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#response-1\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nParameterTypeDescriptiontypestringMessage type (unsubscribed).connection_idstringString identifying the subscription.channelstringFeed type identifier.message_idintMessage sequence number sent on the subscription.idstringSelector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.\\n\",\"title\":\"Response\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\",\"Unsubscribe\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#data\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>After subscription, the incoming messages will be serialized using the following schema.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#data\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nAfter subscription, the incoming messages will be serialized using the following schema.\\n\",\"title\":\"Data\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#json-schema-2\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>connection_id</code></td><td>string</td><td>String identifying the subscription.</td></tr><tr><td><code>channel</code></td><td>string</td><td>Feed type identifier.</td></tr><tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>Selector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.</td></tr><tr><td><code>message_id</code></td><td>int</td><td>Message sequence number sent on the subscription.</td></tr><tr><td><code>version</code></td><td>string</td><td>Protocol identifier.</td></tr><tr><td><code>contents</code></td><td>value</td><td>Channel-specific message data.</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#json-schema-2\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nParameterTypeDescriptionconnection_idstringString identifying the subscription.channelstringFeed type identifier.idstringSelector for channel-specific data. Only used in some channels.message_idintMessage sequence number sent on the subscription.versionstringProtocol identifier.contentsvalueChannel-specific message data.\\n\",\"title\":\"JSON Schema\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\",\"Common schemas\",\"Data\"]},{\"href\":\"/indexer-client/websockets/intro#channels\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The available clients API is presented below.\\nFor each, the subscription and unsubscription functions are shown. Internally, these functions send messages serialized in the <a href=\\\"#json-schema\\\">subscribe</a> and <a href=\\\"#json-schema-1\\\">unsubscribe</a> JSON schemas above.</p>\\n<p>For each channel/feed type the sub-schemas employed in the <code>contents</code> field of the received <a href=\\\"#json-schema-2\\\">Data</a> (after subscription) are shown.</p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/websockets/intro.mdx#channels\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe available clients API is presented below.\\nFor each, the subscription and unsubscription functions are shown. Internally, these functions send messages serialized in the subscribe and unsubscribe JSON schemas above.\\nFor each channel/feed type the sub-schemas employed in the contents field of the received Data (after subscription) are shown.\",\"title\":\"Channels\",\"titles\":[\"WebSockets API\"]}]}}"
